## 5. Talent Tree

Korrath has 3 talent branches, each with 4 tiers. One talent point is granted at run start and one per act boss defeat (up to 4 total).

-----

### Branch 1 — Iron Vanguard

*Focus: Human formation, Armour stacking, patient investment, Guard capstone*

The knight becomes a Human anchor for a disciplined formation. Armour accumulates through Formation triggers and converts directly into ATK. The capstone makes the knight an immovable guardian that doubles all future Armour gains.

|Tier|ID              |Name             |Effect                                                                                                                                                                                                   |
|----|----------------|-----------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|T0  |iron_formation  |Iron Formation   |Abyssal Knight’s race becomes Human. Abyssal Knight gains the Formation keyword: the first time a Human is placed adjacent to the knight, it permanently gains 200 Armour and 200 HP (triggers once only)|
|T1  |commanders_reach|Commander’s Reach|Whenever any friendly minion’s Formation effect triggers, all friendly Human minions on the board permanently gain +50 Armour (stacks across multiple Formation triggers)                                |
|T2  |iron_resolve    |Iron Resolve     |All friendly Humans gain ATK equal to their current Armour value (passive, always active)                                                                                                                |
|T3  |unbreakable     |Unbreakable      |CAPSTONE: Abyssal Knight gains Guard. All Armour gains on Abyssal Knight are doubled                                                                                                                     |

**Branch notes:**

- T0 Formation is a one-time permanent trigger — does not retrigger on subsequent adjacent humans
- T1 listens for any friendly Formation trigger (not just the knight’s). Each trigger permanently buffs every friendly Human currently on the board, so Human-heavy boards with multiple Formation sources snowball Armour fast. The knight is a Human under T0 and receives the +50 itself; T3 doubles the knight’s portion only.
- T2 conversion is a live passive — as Armour changes, ATK updates accordingly
- T3 Guard forces all enemy attacks into the knight; doubled Armour gains amplify T2’s ATK conversion simultaneously
- Branch wants a human-heavy deck from run start, with a clear Armour story: T0 seeds, T1 grows the board, T2 converts to ATK, T3 amplifies the knight axis

-----

### Branch 2 — Runic Knight

*Focus: Double race tag, rune generation through attacks, rune aura absorption, Grand Ritual Chaos capstone*

The knight transcends its origin through runic empowerment, gaining both Human and Demon tags. Every attack generates a random rune. Overflow runes are absorbed as permanent auras. T2 is a sibling tier — Path of Demons (Demon-summon damage) and Path of Humans (Human-summon ATK buff). The capstone fires Grand Ritual: Chaos — three volatile effects with one randomly enhanced post-resolution.

|Tier|ID                 |Name               |Effect                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               |
|----|-------------------|-------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|T0  |runeforge_strike  |Runeforge Strike  |Abyssal Knight gains both Human and Demon race tags simultaneously. Whenever Abyssal Knight attacks, place a random Rune on your board                                                                                                                                                                                                               |
|T1  |runic_absorption  |Runic Absorption  |Whenever a friendly Rune is destroyed or consumed (by overflow, by ritual, by card effects like Runic Substitution, etc.), permanently grant its aura to a random Abyssal Knight on board. Stacks — the same aura type can be granted multiple times. Replaces the old "full-board overflow only" trigger with a general destruction/consumption listener.|
|T2a |path_of_demons    |Path of Demons    |Sibling T2 — whenever a Demon is summoned, deal 50 damage × total active rune auras (rune slots + knight aura stacks) to a random enemy, repeated that many times                                                                                                                                                                                    |
|T2b |path_of_humans    |Path of Humans    |Sibling T2 — whenever a Human is summoned, give 50 ATK × total active rune auras to a random friendly minion, repeated that many times                                                                                                                                                                                                               |
|T3  |grand_ritual_chaos|Grand Ritual: Chaos|CAPSTONE (prereq: `runic_absorption`): Consume any 3 active runes → trigger 3 volatile effects simultaneously. Each effect has inherent damage/value variance (rolls within a range). After all effects resolve, randomly reveal one as Enhanced — its output is massively amplified. T1 triggers three times simultaneously, granting three rune auras to a random Abyssal Knight|

**Rune aura count for T2 (X):**
X = active rune slots on board + total aura stacks absorbed by all Abyssal Knights via T1

**Sibling T2 pattern:**
`path_of_demons` and `path_of_humans` are siblings — both have `runic_absorption` (T1) as prereq, both live in Branch 2. With four total talent picks per run the player can only unlock one in practice.

**T1 interaction with rune destruction events:**
T1 listens broadly on "friendly rune destroyed or consumed." Triggering events include:
- **Overflow** — Knight (or other rune generator) places a rune on a full board → oldest/random rune is destroyed → T1 absorbs.
- **Ritual consumption** — Abyssal Summoning Circle and similar ritual cards consume runes by type → consumed runes feed T1.
- **Card-driven destruction** — Runic Substitution (`korrath_runic_knight`) destroys a player-targeted rune → T1 absorbs.
- **Grand Ritual: Chaos (T3)** — consumes 3 runes → T1 fires 3 times → 3 aura stacks granted to a random Abyssal Knight.
- **Future ritual/card consumption** — any new mechanic that destroys or consumes runes also feeds T1 automatically.

**Branch notes:**

- Random rune generation introduces variance the player adapts to rather than controls
- T2 path choice commits the deck to Demon flood or Human summon identity
- T3 Enhanced reveal happens after all effects resolve — the chaos is embraced, not gamed
- Branch is dependent on the knight attacking consistently; removal stalls rune generation
- Both demon and human paths remain functional without the knight via T2 summon triggers
- T1's broader "destroy/consume → absorb" listener means rune turnover is *valuable* — the player benefits from churning runes through any consumption mechanic, not just hitting overflow

-----

### Branch 3 — Abyssal Breaker

*Focus: Demon knight, corruption as Armour stripper, Armour Break stacking, spell damage explosion capstone*

The knight becomes a Demon and a living corruption engine. Every corruption stack strips enemy Armour. The knight applies corruption on every attack including to the enemy hero. T2 is a sibling tier — Path of Corruption (spell-burst route) and Path of Shattering (demon-aggression route). The capstone detonates accumulated Armour Break as spell damage on enemy death.

|Tier|ID                 |Name               |Effect                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               |
|----|-------------------|-------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|T0  |corrupting_presence|Corrupting Presence|Abyssal Knight’s race becomes Demon. Each stack of Corruption on an enemy also reduces that enemy’s Armour by 100                                                                                                                                                                    |
|T1  |corrupting_strike  |Corrupting Strike  |Whenever Abyssal Knight attacks any target (minion or enemy hero), apply 1 Corruption stack to that target                                                                                                                                                                           |
|T2a |path_of_corruption |Path of Corruption |Sibling T2 — your spells apply 1 Corruption stack to their target on cast; each Corruption stack on a target increases VOID_CORRUPTION spell damage it takes by 100                                                                                                                  |
|T2b |path_of_shattering |Path of Shattering |Sibling T2 — whenever a friendly Demon attacks, apply 50 Armour Break to the target *after* the attack's damage resolves                                                                                                                                                            |
|T3  |shattering_doom    |Shattering Doom    |CAPSTONE (prereq: `corrupting_strike`): When an enemy minion dies, deal spell damage to all enemy minions equal to that minion’s total accumulated Armour Break value                                                                                                                |

**Key interactions:**

- T0 + T1: knight attacks simultaneously deal damage, apply corruption, and strip 100 Armour per stack — two debuff systems from one attack
- Path of Corruption + T3: corruption stacks on surviving enemies increase spell damage taken, amplifying the explosion damage they receive
- Path of Shattering + T3: demon attacks leave 50 AB as a post-damage residual on each strike, so AB accumulates on a target across multiple attacks rather than being consumed on each strip. Shattering Doom reads that accumulated pile on death — the core B3 loop is "attack repeatedly to stack AB, kill the target to detonate."
- T3 explosion is spell damage — bypasses Armour on all targets hit, benefits from Path of Corruption’s corruption amplification
- Branch wants a demon-heavy or spell-heavy deck depending on T2 path chosen

