## 9. Design Notes

- **Textless core unit:** Abyssal Knight’s power comes entirely from branch investment. Early game it is an unremarkable body; mid-to-late game it transforms based on talent choices
- **Three race identities:** Each branch changes the knight’s race at T0 — Human (Branch 1), Human+Demon (Branch 2), Demon (Branch 3). Three completely different deck compositions from the same hero
- **Armour minimum damage floor:** Physical attacks always deal at least 100 damage regardless of Armour value, preventing immunity states
- **Spell penetration:** Spells bypass Armour entirely, providing consistent counterplay for spell-heavy opponents
- **Support card pool:** Hero Core (`korrath_core`) defined in §10; Common Support (`korrath_common`) and three talent-specific pools (`korrath_iron_vanguard`, `korrath_runic_knight`, `korrath_abyssal_breaker`) still pending
- **Starter deck:** Two preset decks shipped — `korrath_iron_legion` (Human-leaning) and `korrath_abyssal_vanguard` (Demon-leaning) — to signal composition choice from hero select

