### Branch payoff matrix

How each core card serves each T0:

|Card                |B1 — Iron Formation (Human Knight)                                         |B2 — Runeforge Strike (Human+Demon Knight)                    |B3 — Corrupting Presence (Demon Knight)                                       |
|--------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|Squire of the Order |Discount lets you drop Knight T2 to set up Formation faster                |Discount + dual-tag body = Formation off Knight itself        |Discount lets you drop Knight T2 to start stacking corruption faster          |
|Order Conscript     |Free Human Formation partner                                               |Generic cheap Human; pairs with Path of Humans T2 triggers    |Generic 1E filler; weakest in B3 but still draws Path of Shattering value as a body|
|Rally the Ranks     |Two adjacent Humans = guaranteed Formation trigger on Knight               |Two adjacent same-race bodies = extra triggers for path T2s  |Two adjacent Demons = AB stacks via Path of Shattering, corruption fuel       |
|Quartermaster       |+100 Armour aura compounds with Iron Resolve (Armour → ATK conversion)     |+100 Armour keeps Knight alive longer = more rune generation  |+100 Armour on every summon keeps Demons alive while corruption stacks        |
|Shatterstrike       |Spot removal that respects the Armour system (mechanic legibility)         |Spot removal; physical damage tag opens future buff surface   |Spot removal; corruption-apply via Path of Corruption still fires on cast     |

### Design notes

- **Squire of the Order** is the Knight-cost-fix the hero needs. Hero passive already discounts the Knight by 1E (4→3E); Squire's Formation drops in-hand Knights by another 2 (3→1E floor, single trigger). The Formation requirement is the gate — you commit a 2E body to the board and arrange adjacency before the discount lands. This rewards Korrath's "patient investment" identity rather than handing the player a flat tempo boost.
- **Order Conscript + Order Footman** is the Human equivalent of Void Imp / Void Demon — a 1E Human filler missing from `abyss_core`. The Footman lives in hand as a "deferred body at 1E," letting the player choose the timing of placement (vs. Void Spawning's auto-placement). This is the only Korrath-flavored way to reliably stack Humans without Branch 1 talent investment.
- **Rally the Ranks** is the Formation enabler — adaptive race tokens mean the spell works in all three deck compositions. The 2M cost is justified by the targeted-adjacency placement (vs. random-slot summon spells like Void Spawning at 1M). Tokens are 200/100 glass cannons so they're disposable Formation triggers, not durable bodies.
- **Quartermaster** is the only aura card in core; it converts "every minion you play" into a +100 Armour event, which is mechanically the strongest non-Knight way to scale into Branch 1 Iron Resolve's ATK conversion. The "does not self-buff" rule prevents the obvious infinite-recursion question at its own summon.
- **Shatterstrike** is the **only physical-school spell in the game** at time of writing — its role is teaching the Armour ↔ Armour Break ↔ physical damage interaction via a single card the player will cast many times. The 400-damage / minion-only profile balances against `flesh_rend` (2M / 300+, hits hero) — Shatterstrike trades hero damage for higher minion damage with a mechanic interaction.

### Act gating

Core cards are unrestricted (all available from Act 1) — same gating model as `abyss_core` and `seris_core`. No talent prerequisites; all unlocked by default once Korrath is the active hero.

### Out of scope for §10

§10 covers `korrath_core` only (deck-builder pool). The rewards-side pools — `korrath_common` (Hero Common Support, branch-agnostic) and the three talent-specific pools (`korrath_iron_vanguard`, `korrath_runic_knight`, `korrath_abyssal_breaker`, each gated behind its branch T0 talent) — are deferred to §11–14. `hero_reward_pool` is left empty — matches Seris precedent (the field is dead code; cleanup tracked in task 013).

Naming convention follows `CARD_POOL_ARCHITECTORE.md § 6` inventory and the Vael precedent (`vael_common`, `vael_piercing_void`, etc.) — talent-specific pool IDs use the branch ID, not a flavor name.

