## 11. Common Support Pool — `korrath_common`

**Pool kind:** Hero Common Support (rewards-side, branch-agnostic — see [`CARD_POOL_ARCHITECTORE.md § 3.1`](CARD_POOL_ARCHITECTORE.md)). Eligible as combat reward / shop offer from the start of any Korrath run, subject to act × rarity gating only — no talent prereq.
**Pool ID:** `korrath_common`
**Visibility:** Korrath-only. Never appears in the deck builder.
**Purpose:** Fill the mechanic-support gaps `korrath_core` (5 cards) is too small to cover. Specifically: more Armour sources, the first Armour Break appliers outside of talents, two new FORMATION-keyword minions (Shield Bearer + Rank Breaker) plus a Formation-cascade payoff (Battle Drillmaster), a Korrath-flavored Rune, a single-target corruption applicator, and a cheap dual-race buff spell. Every card must be playable across all three branches — branch-locked *synergy* is fine when the base card is generically useful (Creeping Blight is the canonical case — see card #8 in design notes).

The pool deliberately stays light on rune-generation (those live in `abyss_core` + B2). Corruption gets one entry (Creeping Blight) as a single-target spell that doesn't duplicate the AoE/random-target corruption sources already in `abyss_core`. The pool **leans heavier on Formation than originally planned** (three FORMATION cards: Shield Bearer, Rank Breaker, Drillmaster's cascade) because Formation is Korrath's most distinctive mechanic and was underrepresented in `korrath_core` (only Squire of the Order carries it).

