### Design notes

- **Shield Squire** is the **cheap Human Formation seed** the branch needs — 1E for 100/200 with a self-Armour FORMATION trigger. Slightly stronger than Order Conscript (1E vanilla 100/100 + adds a Footman to hand) in raw stats and built-in mechanic, justified by the talent-gated pool tier. Pairs with the Knight as a same-race Formation partner — Knight's T0 fires (+200 Armour, +200 HP), and Squire's own Formation fires on the same adjacency (Squire +100 Armour). Two simultaneous Formation events on one drop = double T1 trigger (if T1 is taken).
- **Vanguard Marshal** is the **card-draw Formation listener** — 3E for 200/400 + a passive that draws a card every time any friendly FORMATION triggers. Card draw is the rarest commodity in the game and per-trigger card draw is **unprecedented**. The cost-justification chain: (a) requires Formation events to happen — Marshal does nothing in a non-Formation deck; (b) the player has to invest in Formation density (Knight + Squire + Shield Bearer + Lord Commander + Rank Breaker + Battle Drillmaster) to fuel Marshal; (c) Marshal itself is a 200/400 body that dies easily to mid-game removal so the draw engine has a real lifespan constraint. **Power-level flag for balance sim:** in a maximally-stacked B1 board with 5-6 dormant Formations triggered in one Drillmaster cascade, Marshal can draw 5-6 cards in one event chain. If sim shows this is oppressive, the dial is: (i) once-per-turn cap (1 draw per turn regardless of Formation count), (ii) cost bump to 4E, or (iii) +200 HP body trade for "draw a card only when Marshal's *own* Formation triggers" (would require adding FORMATION to Marshal).
- **Shield Bash** is the **scaling damage spell** — 1M PHYSICAL spell, single-target, damage = sum of (every friendly minion's current Armour value + your hero's current Armour value). At T0 with a Formation'd Knight (+200 Armour) and a Quartermaster-buffed board (couple of +100 Armour minions), damage is in the 400-500 range — already competitive with Void Bolt (2M / 500). At late B1 with T3-doubled Knight (~800 Armour), Commander's +200 hero Armour, Bastion Rune drip on Humans, etc., the total can hit 1000-1500 for a 1M cast — **easily the strongest non-Knight finisher in the deck**. PHYSICAL school routes through enemy Armour math (§2) which is a small mitigation (≤ enemy AB stripped or armour value). Armour values used by Shield Bash are **not consumed** — the spell reads them as a counter, it does not spend them. **Power-level flag for balance sim:** this card scales with the *exact thing the branch builds toward*, which is the design intent — Shield Bash *is* the Armour-cash-out spell. Sim will likely show it's the marquee card. If too strong, dial: (i) cap damage at 800, (ii) bump cost to 2M, (iii) only count minion Armour (exclude hero), or (iv) split — half goes to the target, half to all enemies. User chose 1M cost deliberately; flagged for monitoring, not preemptively nerfed.
- **Lord Commander** is the **hero-Armour swing card** — 5E for 300/500 Human + ON PLAY: your hero gains 200 Armour. The hero-Armour grant is the design centerpiece — hero Armour is one of the strongest defensive states in the game (every incoming attack reduced by 200, floored at 100 — see §6 + task 007). At 5E this is the Knight-tier price point, justified by no FORMATION setup requirement (Knight needs adjacency to trigger T0; Commander just plays). Compare to Quartermaster (3E 200/400 + per-summon +100 Armour aura on minions): Commander trades the aura and 1 race tier for a one-shot 200 hero Armour and 100 ATK / 100 HP, at +2E. Combo: every point of Commander's hero Armour feeds Shield Bash's damage (Shield Bash reads hero Armour as a counter), so Commander + Shield Bash same turn is +200 damage on Bash for the rest of combat. Iron Resolve (T2) does **not** convert hero Armour to ATK — that's minion-only — so Commander's hero Armour stays purely defensive on its own; pairing with Shield Bash is what cashes it into offense.
- **Oath of Iron** is the **board-fill cascade spell** — 3M Epic. Fills every empty slot on the player's board with Iron Footman (200/200 Human) tokens. Each placement is a fresh summon that follows normal FORMATION rules (per §2) — if a Footman lands adjacent to a dormant FORMATION minion of the same race, that Formation fires for the first time. This is the **B1 cash-out**: on a typical mid-game B1 turn, the player has ~2-3 empty slots. Oath of Iron fills them with 200/200 bodies (so +400-600 ATK + +400-600 effective HP in tempo), and each new Footman that lands adjacent to the Knight / Shield Bearer / Lord Commander / etc. fires their dormant Formations. With T1 (Commander's Reach), each Formation event grants every friendly Human +50 Armour. Stacked with T2 (Iron Resolve), all that new Armour converts to ATK on every Human including the Knight. 3M cost is the same as Oath's prior iteration (Knight finisher); the new design is *broader* but loses the SWIFT/double-attack focus. Compare to Void Spawning (1M, 2× 100/100 tokens) — Oath gives ~5× the bodies, 4× the ATK per body, plus Formation cascade, at 3× the cost. **Power-level flag for balance sim:** combined with Vanguard Marshal (per-Formation card draw) and Battle Drillmaster (Formation cascade), Oath of Iron in a B1 deck can resolve into a multi-card-draw, multi-Formation, board-filled turn for 3M. Likely the most game-ending single card in the pool. If too strong, dial: (i) cost bump to 4M / 5M, (ii) reduce to "fill up to 3 slots" instead of all empty, (iii) drop Footman stats to 100/100, (iv) Footmen do not trigger Formation. User chose 3M and Yes-to-Formation deliberately; flagged for monitoring.

### Ruling notes

- **Shield Squire's FORMATION** is the same engine as other FORMATION minions — same-race adjacency required, one-time trigger per pair, etc. (§2).
- **Vanguard Marshal's passive** listens on `ON_FORMATION_TRIGGERED` (already in the trigger enum per Enums.gd) — fires regardless of which minion's Formation just triggered. Marshal doesn't have FORMATION as a keyword, so it never self-triggers. Multiple Marshals on board each draw a card per Formation event (e.g. 2 Marshals + 1 Formation trigger = 2 cards drawn). Draw resolves through the standard card-draw pipeline (deck → hand; if hand is full, the card is burned per the standard overdraw rule).
- **Shield Bash's damage source** is each minion's `armour` field plus the hero's Armour stat (per §6). Reads the value at cast time — does **not** consume Armour. Spell damage school is PHYSICAL, which routes through enemy Armour math (§2 linter rules). Negative friendly Armour values (rare — would require an enemy AB-on-hero effect that doesn't exist yet) would *reduce* Shield Bash damage; in practice friendly Armour is always ≥ 0.
- **Lord Commander's hero Armour grant** uses the same hero-Armour pipeline as the existing handlers from task 007 (PR1-3) — calls `state.apply_hero_buff("player", Enums.BuffType.ARMOUR, 200, "lord_commander")`. Permanent until removed by hero-side AB.
- **Oath of Iron Formation interaction:** each Footman is summoned via the standard summon path (`combat_state.summon_minion(...)`), so it triggers `ON_FORMATION_TRIGGERED` (and `ON_PLAYER_MINION_SUMMONED` etc.) for any neighboring FORMATION minion of the same race. Order of summoning across multiple empty slots: left-to-right slot order, deterministic. If a Footman in slot 2 fires the Knight's Formation in slot 3, that Formation is fully resolved before the slot-3-or-later Footman is summoned. Each Footman is treated as an independent summon for trigger purposes.
- **Iron Footman vs Order Footman:** these are **different tokens** sharing a similar name. Iron Footman is 200/200 (Oath of Iron's output), Order Footman is 100/200 (`korrath_core`'s Order Conscript adds it to hand). Both are Human; neither has effect text. Naming the new token "Iron Footman" rather than reusing "Order Footman" prevents the player's intuition that drawing Oath gives them more in-hand Footmen from Order Conscript (it doesn't — Oath bypasses hand and summons directly to the board).

